README.md
     1‚Üísemver(1) -- The semantic versioner for npm
     4‚Üí## Install
     6‚Üí```bash
     7‚Üínpm install semver
     8‚Üí````
     9‚Üí
    10‚Üí## Usage
    12‚ÜíAs a node module:
    13‚Üí
    14‚Üí```js
    15‚Üíconst semver = require('semver')
    16‚Üí
    17‚Üísemver.valid('1.2.3') // '1.2.3'
    18‚Üísemver.valid('a.b.c') // null
    19‚Üísemver.clean('  =v1.2.3   ') // '1.2.3'
    20‚Üísemver.satisfies('1.2.3', '1.x || >=2.5.0 || 5.0.0 - 7.2.3') // true
    21‚Üísemver.gt('1.2.3', '9.8.7') // false
    22‚Üísemver.lt('1.2.3', '9.8.7') // true
    23‚Üísemver.minVersion('>=1.0.0') // '1.0.0'
    24‚Üísemver.valid(semver.coerce('v2')) // '2.0.0'
    25‚Üísemver.valid(semver.coerce('42.6.7.9.3-alpha')) // '42.6.7'
    26‚Üí```
    27‚Üí
    28‚ÜíYou can also just load the module for the function that you care about if
    29‚Üíyou'd like to minimize your footprint.
    30‚Üí
    31‚Üí```js
    32‚Üí// load the whole API at once in a single object
    33‚Üíconst semver = require('semver')
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   139‚Üí## Versions
   141‚ÜíA "version" is described by the `v2.0.0` specification found at
   142‚Üí<https://semver.org/>.
   143‚Üí
   144‚ÜíA leading `"="` or `"v"` character is stripped off and ignored.
   145‚ÜíSupport for stripping a leading "v" is kept for compatibility with `v1.0.0` of the SemVer
   146‚Üíspecification but should not be used anymore.
   147‚Üí
   148‚Üí## Ranges
   150‚ÜíA `version range` is a set of `comparators` that specify versions
   151‚Üíthat satisfy the range.
   152‚Üí
   153‚ÜíA `comparator` is composed of an `operator` and a `version`.  The set
   154‚Üíof primitive `operators` is:
   155‚Üí
   156‚Üí* `<` Less than
   157‚Üí* `<=` Less than or equal to
   158‚Üí* `>` Greater than
   159‚Üí* `>=` Greater than or equal to
   160‚Üí* `=` Equal.  If no operator is specified, then equality is assumed,
   161‚Üí  so this operator is optional but MAY be included.
   162‚Üí
   163‚ÜíFor example, the comparator `>=1.2.7` would match the versions
   164‚Üí`1.2.7`, `1.2.8`, `2.5.3`, and `1.3.9`, but not the versions `1.2.6`
   165‚Üíor `1.1.0`. The comparator `>1` is equivalent to `>=2.0.0` and
   166‚Üíwould match the versions `2.0.0` and `3.1.0`, but not the versions
   167‚Üí`1.0.1` or `1.1.0`.
   168‚Üí
   169‚ÜíComparators can be joined by whitespace to form a `comparator set`,
   170‚Üíwhich is satisfied by the **intersection** of all of the comparators
   171‚Üíit includes.
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   184‚Üí### Prerelease Tags
   219‚Üí#### Prerelease Identifiers
   250‚Üí#### Prerelease Identifier Base
   279‚Üí### Advanced Range Syntax
   287‚Üí#### Hyphen Ranges `X.Y.Z - A.B.C`
   306‚Üí#### X-Ranges `1.2.x` `1.X` `1.2.*` `*`
   324‚Üí#### Tilde Ranges `~1.2.3` `~1.2` `~1`
   341‚Üí#### Caret Ranges `^1.2.3` `^0.2.5` `^0.0.4`
   384‚Üí### Range Grammar
   408‚Üí## Functions
   410‚ÜíAll methods and classes take a final `options` object argument.  All
   411‚Üíoptions in this object are `false` by default.  The options supported
   412‚Üíare:
   413‚Üí
   414‚Üí- `loose`: Be more forgiving about not-quite-valid semver strings.
   415‚Üí  (Any resulting output will always be 100% strict compliant, of
   416‚Üí  course.)  For backwards compatibility reasons, if the `options`
   417‚Üí  argument is a boolean value instead of an object, it is interpreted
   418‚Üí  to be the `loose` param.
   419‚Üí- `includePrerelease`: Set to suppress the [default
   420‚Üí  behavior](https://github.com/npm/node-semver#prerelease-tags) of
   421‚Üí  excluding prerelease tagged versions from ranges unless they are
   422‚Üí  explicitly opted into.
   423‚Üí
   424‚ÜíStrict-mode Comparators and Ranges will be strict about the SemVer
   425‚Üístrings that they parse.
   426‚Üí
   427‚Üí* `valid(v)`: Return the parsed version, or null if it's not valid.
   428‚Üí* `inc(v, releaseType, options, identifier, identifierBase)`: 
   429‚Üí  Return the version incremented by the release
   430‚Üí  type (`major`, `premajor`, `minor`, `preminor`, `patch`,
   431‚Üí  `prepatch`, `prerelease`, or `release`), or null if it's not valid
      ‚Üí  ‚Ä¶
   453‚Üí### Comparison
   478‚Üí### Sorting
   485‚Üí### Comparators
   489‚Üí### Ranges
   531‚Üí### Coercion
   558‚Üí### Clean
   576‚Üí## Constants
   578‚ÜíAs a convenience, helper constants are exported to provide information about what `node-semver` supports:
   579‚Üí
   580‚Üí### `RELEASE_TYPES`
   600‚Üí### `SEMVER_SPEC_VERSION`
   610‚Üí## Exported Modules
   613‚ÜíTODO: Make sure that all of these items are documented (classes aren't,
   614‚Üíeg), and then pull the module name into the documentation for that specific
   615‚Üíthing.
   616‚Üí-->
   617‚Üí
   618‚ÜíYou may pull in just the part of this semver utility that you need if you
   619‚Üíare sensitive to packing and tree-shaking concerns.  The main
   620‚Üí`require('semver')` export uses getter functions to lazily load the parts
   621‚Üíof the API that are used.
   622‚Üí
   623‚ÜíThe following modules are available:
   624‚Üí
   625‚Üí* `require('semver')`
   626‚Üí* `require('semver/classes')`
   627‚Üí* `require('semver/classes/comparator')`
   628‚Üí* `require('semver/classes/range')`
   629‚Üí* `require('semver/classes/semver')`
   630‚Üí* `require('semver/functions/clean')`
   631‚Üí* `require('semver/functions/cmp')`
   632‚Üí* `require('semver/functions/coerce')`
   633‚Üí* `require('semver/functions/compare')`
   634‚Üí* `require('semver/functions/compare-build')`
